25|$|During the {{coalition}} government's brief tenure {{and one year}} afterwards, due to the protracted lack of a permanent central authority, the Fund <b>For</b> <b>Peace's</b> Fragile States <b>Index</b> (FSI; {{formerly known as the}} Failed States Index) listed Somalia on top for six consecutive years between 2008 and 2013. In 2009, Transparency International ranked the nation in last place on its annual Corruption Perceptions Index (CPI), a metric that purports to show the prevalence of corruption in a country's public sector. In mid-2010, the Institute <b>for</b> Economics and <b>Peace</b> also ranked Somalia in the next-to-last position in between war-afflicted Iraq and Afghanistan on its Global <b>Peace</b> <b>Index.</b>|$|R
